-- в”Ђв”Ђ ASUS в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$ASUS is a Taiwanese multinational technology company that designs and manufactures laptops, desktops, motherboards, graphics cards, monitors, networking gear, and the ROG gaming brand.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE(NULL, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(1989, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$approx 16,000+ employees worldwide$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Beitou District, Taipei, Taiwan$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$ASUS Overview 2026: Products, History and Hardware Lineup$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$ASUS is a Taiwan-based hardware maker known for motherboards, laptops, ROG gaming gear, monitors and routers. See its history, product lines and scale for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$ASUS, formally ASUSTeK Computer Inc, is a Taiwanese multinational computer hardware and electronics company founded in Taipei in 1989 by four engineers, Tzu-Hsien Tung, Ted Hsu, Wayne Hsieh, and M.T. Liao, who had previously worked together at Acer. The company started by building PC motherboards and grew into one of the world's largest technology hardware manufacturers, headquartered in the Beitou District of Taipei, Taiwan, with tens of thousands of employees globally and tens of billions of dollars in annual revenue. ASUS is not a single software product but a diversified hardware company whose relevant product lines for a technology directory include desktop and laptop motherboards, prebuilt and custom desktop PCs, Windows laptops (including the ZenBook and VivoBook lines), the Eee PC netbook series that helped popularize affordable ultraportable laptops starting in 2007, monitors and displays, graphics cards, networking equipment such as WiFi routers and mesh systems, and components for creators and professionals under lines like ProArt. Its best-known sub-brand is Republic of Gamers, or ROG, launched in 2006 and now one of the most recognized names in PC gaming hardware, spanning gaming laptops, motherboards, graphics cards, monitors, peripherals, and handheld gaming devices, alongside sponsorship of esports teams and tournaments. ASUS also owns a majority stake in graphics card and motherboard maker ASRock and has historically had close ties to chip and device joint ventures in the Taiwanese electronics supply chain. Because ASUS sells thousands of individual SKUs across wildly different price points, from budget routers and entry motherboards to flagship gaming laptops and workstation-class hardware, there is no single starting price or subscription model; pricing is set per product and varies by region and retailer. The company competes broadly with other PC and component makers such as Acer, Lenovo, Dell, HP, MSI, and Gigabyte, and within gaming specifically ROG competes with brand lines like MSI's own gaming division and Razer. ASUS's core audience spans everyday consumers buying laptops and routers, PC enthusiasts and gamers building or buying systems, and IT departments and system integrators sourcing motherboards and components at scale. The company is publicly traded on the Taiwan Stock Exchange and remains one of the most influential hardware brands in the global PC ecosystem, particularly in motherboards and gaming laptops.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '07218b04-d5e0-4c15-b183-87a769bfbbc2';

